result.execSummary:
The defendant Stephanie Jean Pate was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Stephanie Jean Pate is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Stephanie Jean Pate was found guilty of Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Cases called: 16CM441, 15CM672 & 16CM574, Defendant Stephanie Jean Pate in court with attorney Peter Michael Masana.  Troy D Cross appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court went over the rights & elements. Defendant pled no contest to count 2 in 15CM672, count 3 in 16CM574, count 1 in 16CM441. Court found defendant guilty, entered judgment, sentence withheld, 2 years probation. Conditions: Complete anger management.  Maintain absolute sobriety.  Submit DNA sample. Complete an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment recommendations. In 15CM672, $553 costs, 16CM441, $443, 16CM574, $443 costs. No jail credit. All other counts dismissed.
